---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Smart Investment Options - Bonds, FD & Mutual Funds | TrueCred Loan Expert">

<!-- Page Hero -->
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span>Investments</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Smart <span class="gradient-text">Investment Options</span></h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Grow your wealth with curated investment options including Bonds, Fixed Deposits, and Mutual Funds. Expert-guided strategies for every risk appetite and financial goal.</p>
      <div class="hero-highlights">
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-shield-halved"></i>
          <span>SEBI Regulated</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-percent"></i>
          <span>Up to 8% Returns</span>
        </div>
        <div class="highlight-item">
          <i class="fas fa-user-tie"></i>
          <span>Expert Guidance</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page Content -->
  <section class="page-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="content-grid">

        <!-- Main Content -->
        <div class="content-main">

          <!-- Overview -->
          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header">
              <span class="section-tag">Overview</span>
              <h2>Why Invest with TrueCred?</h2>
            </div>
            <p>Investing is the key to building long-term wealth and achieving your financial goals — whether it's buying a home, funding your child's education, or planning for a comfortable retirement. At TrueCred, we offer a carefully curated selection of investment options that cater to every risk appetite and investment horizon.</p>
            <p>Our platform provides access to SEBI-regulated investment products with complete transparency, expert guidance, and seamless digital experience. Whether you prefer the safety of fixed deposits, the steady returns of bonds, or the growth potential of mutual funds, we have the right solution for you.</p>
            <p>All investments on our platform are backed by trusted financial institutions and regulated by appropriate authorities. Our team of certified financial advisors is always available to help you make informed investment decisions based on your unique financial situation.</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Investment Returns Info Grid -->
          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header">
              <span class="section-tag">Returns Overview</span>
              <h2>Compare Investment Returns</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="info-grid">
              <div class="info-box">
                <div class="info-value" style="color: #3b82f6;">7–9%</div>
                <div class="info-label">Bonds</div>
                <p>Stable fixed-income returns with government and corporate bond options. Ideal for conservative investors seeking steady income.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="info-box">
                <div class="info-value" style="color: #22c55e;">Up to 8%</div>
                <div class="info-label">Fixed Deposits</div>
                <p>Guaranteed returns with flexible tenure options from top banks and NBFCs. Capital protection with predictable income.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="info-box">
                <div class="info-value" style="color: #8b5cf6;">Market-Linked</div>
                <div class="info-label">Mutual Funds</div>
                <p>Potential for higher returns through diversified portfolios managed by expert fund managers. Suitable for long-term wealth creation.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Bonds Section -->
          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header">
              <span class="section-tag">Bonds</span>
              <h2>Bond Investment Options</h2>
            </div>
            <p>Bonds are fixed-income securities where you lend money to a government or corporation in exchange for regular interest payments and return of principal at maturity. They are among the safest investment options and are ideal for investors looking for stable, predictable returns.</p>

            <h3>Types of Bonds Available</h3>
            <ul class="feature-list">
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Corporate Bonds</strong>
                  <p>Issued by companies to raise capital for expansion and operations. Corporate bonds typically offer higher interest rates than government bonds (7%–10%) to compensate for the slightly higher credit risk. They are rated by agencies like CRISIL, ICRA, and CARE to help investors assess risk levels.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Government Bonds (G-Secs)</strong>
                  <p>Issued by the Government of India, these bonds are considered the safest investment option as they carry sovereign guarantee. Returns range from 6.5%–7.5% per annum with tenures ranging from 5 to 40 years. They are ideal for long-term, risk-averse investors.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Tax-Free Bonds</strong>
                  <p>Issued by government-backed entities like NHAI, REC, and IRFC, these bonds offer interest income that is completely exempt from income tax. While the coupon rate may appear lower (5.5%–6.5%), the effective post-tax yield is significantly higher for investors in higher tax brackets.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Sovereign Gold Bonds (SGBs)</strong>
                  <p>Issued by the RBI on behalf of the Government of India, SGBs allow you to invest in gold without the hassles of physical storage. You earn an additional 2.5% annual interest on top of gold price appreciation. Capital gains on redemption at maturity are tax-free.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <!-- Fixed Deposits Section -->
          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header">
              <span class="section-tag">Fixed Deposits</span>
              <h2>Fixed Deposit Interest Rates</h2>
            </div>
            <p>Fixed Deposits (FDs) are one of the most popular investment options in India, offering guaranteed returns, capital safety, and flexible tenure options. Compare FD interest rates from top banks and financial institutions to find the best deal for your savings.</p>

            <table class="rate-table">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Bank / Institution</th>
                  <th>Regular FD Rate</th>
                  <th>Senior Citizen Rate</th>
                  <th>Tenure</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>State Bank of India</strong></td>
                  <td>6.50% – 7.10%</td>
                  <td>7.00% – 7.60%</td>
                  <td>1 – 10 years</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>HDFC Bank</strong></td>
                  <td>6.60% – 7.25%</td>
                  <td>7.10% – 7.75%</td>
                  <td>1 – 10 years</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>ICICI Bank</strong></td>
                  <td>6.50% – 7.20%</td>
                  <td>7.00% – 7.70%</td>
                  <td>1 – 10 years</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Axis Bank</strong></td>
                  <td>6.50% – 7.15%</td>
                  <td>7.00% – 7.65%</td>
                  <td>1 – 10 years</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Kotak Mahindra Bank</strong></td>
                  <td>6.50% – 7.30%</td>
                  <td>7.00% – 7.80%</td>
                  <td>1 – 10 years</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Bajaj Finance FD</strong></td>
                  <td>7.25% – 8.05%</td>
                  <td>7.50% – 8.30%</td>
                  <td>1 – 5 years</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td><strong>Post Office FD</strong></td>
                  <td>6.90% – 7.50%</td>
                  <td>6.90% – 7.50%</td>
                  <td>1 – 5 years</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
            <p><em>*Rates are indicative and subject to change. Last updated: April 2026. Senior citizens typically get an additional 0.25%–0.50% over regular rates.</em></p>
          </div>

          <!-- Mutual Funds Section -->
          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header">
              <span class="section-tag">Mutual Funds</span>
              <h2>Mutual Fund Investment Options</h2>
            </div>
            <p>Mutual Funds pool money from multiple investors and invest in a diversified portfolio of stocks, bonds, or other securities. They are managed by professional fund managers and offer an excellent way to participate in the financial markets with relatively small investment amounts.</p>

            <h3>Types of Mutual Funds</h3>
            <ul class="feature-list">
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Large Cap Funds</strong>
                  <p>Invest in top 100 companies by market capitalization. These funds offer relatively stable returns with lower volatility, making them suitable for conservative equity investors. Expected returns: 10%–14% per annum over 5+ years.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Mid Cap Funds</strong>
                  <p>Invest in companies ranked 101–250 by market capitalization. They offer a balance between growth potential and risk. Ideal for investors with a moderate risk appetite and investment horizon of 5–7 years. Expected returns: 12%–18% per annum.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Small Cap Funds</strong>
                  <p>Invest in companies ranked beyond 250 by market capitalization. These funds carry higher risk but also offer the highest growth potential among equity funds. Best suited for aggressive investors with a 7+ year horizon. Expected returns: 15%–25% per annum.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>ELSS (Tax Saving) Funds</strong>
                  <p>Equity Linked Savings Scheme funds offer dual benefits — wealth creation through equity exposure and tax savings under Section 80C (up to ₹1.5 Lakh per year). They come with a 3-year lock-in period, the shortest among tax-saving instruments.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Debt Mutual Funds</strong>
                  <p>Invest in fixed-income securities like government bonds, corporate bonds, and money market instruments. They offer more stable returns than equity funds with lower risk. Ideal for conservative investors or those with short-term goals (1–3 years).</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                <div>
                  <strong>Hybrid / Balanced Funds</strong>
                  <p>Invest in a mix of equity and debt instruments, offering the growth potential of stocks with the stability of bonds. Aggressive hybrid funds allocate 65%–80% to equity, while conservative hybrid funds allocate 75%–90% to debt.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <!-- How to Start Investing -->
          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header">
              <span class="section-tag">Get Started</span>
              <h2>How to Start Investing</h2>
            </div>
            <p>Starting your investment journey with TrueCred is simple and straightforward. Follow these steps to begin building your wealth today.</p>
            <div class="steps-grid">
              <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-num">1</div>
                <h3>Assess Your Goals</h3>
                <p>Define your financial goals, investment horizon, and risk tolerance. Our advisors can help you create a personalized investment plan.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-num">2</div>
                <h3>Choose Products</h3>
                <p>Select from bonds, fixed deposits, or mutual funds based on your goals. Diversify across asset classes for optimal risk-adjusted returns.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-num">3</div>
                <h3>Complete KYC</h3>
                <p>Complete your KYC verification online with PAN, Aadhaar, and bank details. The entire process takes just 5 minutes.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="step-card">
                <div class="step-num">4</div>
                <h3>Start Investing</h3>
                <p>Make your first investment with as little as ₹500 via SIP or lump sum. Track your portfolio performance in real-time on our platform.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div class="content-sidebar">

          <!-- Investment Advisory Form -->
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-chart-pie"></i> Investment Advisory</h3>
            <form class="sidebar-form" onsubmit="return false;">
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="Your Name" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="tel" class="form-input" placeholder="Mobile Number" maxlength="10" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <input type="text" class="form-input" placeholder="Investment Amount (₹)" required>
              </div>
              <div class="form-group">
                <select class="form-input" required>
                  <option value="" disabled selected>Investment Type</option>
                  <option value="bonds">Bonds</option>
                  <option value="fd">Fixed Deposits</option>
                  <option value="mf">Mutual Funds</option>
                  <option value="sip">SIP (Systematic Investment Plan)</option>
                  <option value="nps">National Pension Scheme</option>
                  <option value="gold">Sovereign Gold Bonds</option>
                  <option value="other">Other / Not Sure</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-block" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;">
                Get Advice <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
              </button>
              <p class="form-disclaimer">
                <i class="fas fa-lock"></i> Free consultation. No obligations.
              </p>
            </form>
          </div>

          <!-- Quick Links -->
          <div class="sidebar-card">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-link"></i> Quick Links</h3>
            <ul class="sidebar-links">
              <li><a href="/pages/personal-loan"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Personal Loan</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/business-loan"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Business Loan</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/home-loan"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Home Loan</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/credit-cards"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Credit Cards</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/credit-score"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Credit Score</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/calculators"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> SIP Calculator</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/gold-loan"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Gold Loan</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pages/insurance"><i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i> Insurance Plans</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>

        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-tag">FAQs</span>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions About Investments</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>What is the minimum amount needed to start investing?</span>
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>You can start investing with as little as ₹500 per month through a Systematic Investment Plan (SIP) in mutual funds. For fixed deposits, most banks require a minimum of ₹5,000 to ₹10,000. Bonds typically have a minimum investment of ₹10,000. Sovereign Gold Bonds start at 1 gram of gold (approximately ₹6,000–₹7,000). The key is to start early, even with small amounts, to benefit from the power of compounding.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>Which is better — FD, Bonds, or Mutual Funds?</span>
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>The best investment depends on your financial goals, risk tolerance, and time horizon. Fixed Deposits are ideal for capital preservation with guaranteed returns (6.5%–8%). Bonds offer slightly higher fixed returns (7%–9%) with moderate risk. Mutual Funds provide the highest growth potential (10%–18% historically) but carry market risk. For most investors, a diversified portfolio combining all three asset classes is recommended for optimal risk-adjusted returns.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>Are investments on TrueCred safe and regulated?</span>
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>Yes, absolutely. All investment products on TrueCred are offered through SEBI-registered intermediaries and regulated financial institutions. Fixed Deposits from banks are insured up to ₹5 Lakh by DICGC. Government Bonds and Sovereign Gold Bonds carry sovereign guarantee. Mutual Funds are regulated by SEBI with strict compliance requirements. We partner only with reputed institutions with strong track records to ensure the safety of your investments.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>What are the tax benefits of different investments?</span>
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>Different investments offer various tax benefits. ELSS Mutual Funds provide deduction up to ₹1.5 Lakh under Section 80C with just 3 years lock-in. Tax-Free Bonds offer completely tax-exempt interest income. 5-year Tax Saving FDs qualify for Section 80C deduction. Sovereign Gold Bonds provide tax-free capital gains on maturity plus 2.5% annual interest. NPS contributions qualify for additional ₹50,000 deduction under Section 80CCD(1B) over and above the ₹1.5 Lakh limit.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-question">
            <span>How do I track my investment performance?</span>
            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">
              <p>TrueCred provides a comprehensive portfolio dashboard where you can track all your investments in real-time. You can view current values, returns earned, asset allocation, and performance charts. We also send monthly portfolio reports via email and SMS alerts for significant changes. For mutual funds, you can additionally track performance through the AMC websites or apps like MFCentral and CAMS. Our financial advisors also provide quarterly portfolio review sessions to ensure your investments are on track.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Page CTA -->
  <section class="page-cta">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Start Your Investment Journey Today</h2>
      <p>Get expert-guided investment advice and access to the best Bonds, FDs, and Mutual Funds. Start with as low as ₹500.</p>
      <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">
        Invest Now <i class="fas fa-arrow-right"></i>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Footer -->

</BaseLayout>
